yawa, the state commissioner for Health among others.” “All the patients have tested negative for the disease after the two follow up tests and have, therefore, reached full recovery,” the commissioner stated. He advised the public to continue to observe the strictest personal hygiene through regular hand washing, use of face mask and social distancing. Meanwhile, the former Commissioner for Works in Kano State who was infamously known for his cynical social media post on Abba Kyari’s death has tested positive for COVID-19. He was sacked by the state governor, Umar Ganduje after making the comment.  Engr. Muazu Magaji broke the news of his health status on Facebook, Wednesday morning. Vanguard By Rasheed Sobowale Kano State Commissioner for Health, Dr Aminu Tsanyawa on Thursday reported that 22 out of the 25 suspected cases of the coronavirus (COVID-19) disease in the state has tested negative for the virus.  This was according to a Twitter post by Bashir Ahmad, a Personal Assistant on… April 2, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" Despite spread of coronavirus in Kano, the state government has suspended testing, citing lack of facilities. This came on a day members of Sokoto State Response Team on COVID-19 expressed shock as to how the index case in the state contracted the virus, despite not having any travel history to states… April 23, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" By Bashir Bello and Abdulmumin Murtala - Kano The Kano State Commissioner for Health, Dr. Aminu Ibrahim Tsanyawa on Wednesday says three suspected cases of Coronavirus recorded in the state have tested negative. Tsanyawa stated this while briefing newsmen in the state to allay fears and rumour making rounds on… March 18, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates"